96418.name: Exports to lower-middle income grouping (CEPII (2016))
96418.description:
The share of exports from each entity exported to the lower-middle income country grouping. Income groupings are determined according to the World Bank's 2016 income classification. 

Where the entity is a country, export shares are calculated as a proportion of the country's GDP. 
Where the entity is either an income class grouping, OWID continental grouping, or the World, export shares are calculated as a proportion of World GDP. World GDP consists of individual countries' GDP summed together for each year.
96418.datasetName: Split of exports to different country groups - CEPII (2016)
96418.s_name: CEPII (2016) Two Centuries of Bilateral Trade and Gravity Data: 1827-2014 (2016)

source.name: CEPII (2016) Two Centuries of Bilateral Trade and Gravity Data: 1827-2014 (2016)
source.dataPublishedBy: Michel Fouquin & Jules Hugot , 2016. "Two Centuries of Bilateral Trade and Gravity Data: 1827-2014," CEPII Working Paper 2016- 14 , May 2016 , CEPII
source.dataPublisherSource: IMF Direction of Trade Statistics data set, manuscripts
source.additionalInfo:
To calculate country exports to the rest of the world, the total value of exports by country, per year, is divided by the country's GDP. 

The time series 'World' corresponds to the World's total exports to the rest of the world. The total exports to the World consist of country exports in the sample summed together, then divided by the world GDP for the same year, and multiplied by 100. World GDP is the sum of all countries' GDP for a particular year. 

The total export values of regional income aggregates as a share of world GDP have been calculated using the World Bank's income groupings. The World Bank has four income classifications: High income, Upper-middle income, Lower-middle income, and Low income. The total value of exported goods sums for High income countries, for example, sums together the export values for countries belonging to this income classification, by year. This is then divided by World GDP, calculated by summing together all countries' GDP for a particular year. 

The value of global exports as a share of World GDP have also been calculated for OWID continental groupings. Again, the total value of exports are summed together for each continent, for each year, and are then divided by World GDP. 

Germany's time series is comprised of West Germany, and Germany. East Germany has been excluded for the purposes of Germany's calculations but is included in the World series.
Russia's time series comprises Russia and the USSR.
